The paper deals with the problem of tensor completion, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves analyzing the manifold structure of tensors, which is a topic in differential geometry and topology (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial methods for deriving lower bounds on the sampling probability, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and algorithms (cs.SI).
